li.al:
“Member of the Tribunal” means an elected member of the
                Tribunal or a person chosen under article 17 of the Statute for
                the purpose of a particular case;

the Tribunal shall be free to transfer its funds, gold or
                  its currency from one country to another or within any country
                  and to convert any currency held by it into any other currency;

together with members of their families forming part of their
                household, exemption from immigration restrictions or alien
                registration;

the same privileges in respect of currency and exchange
                facilities as are accorded to the officials of comparable rank
                forming part of diplomatic missions to the Government concerned;

the same facilities in respect of currency and exchange
                restrictions as are accorded to representatives of foreign
                Governments on temporary official missions;

the same facilities in respect of their personal baggage and
                in respect of currency or exchange restrictions as are accorded
                to representatives of foreign Governments on temporary official missions;
